in Russia.<ref>[http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/62691 Meeting on measures to counter the spread of coronavirus in Russia]</ref>\n | image2 = State Council on countering the spread of coronavirus1.jpg\n | caption2 = On 16 March, Mayor of Moscow [[Sergei Sobyanin]] held the first meeting of the State Council working group on countering the spread of coronavirus.\n | footer = \n}}\n\nRussia implemented preventive measures to curb the spread of COVID-19 in the country by imposing quarantines, carrying raids on potential virus carriers and using facial recognition to impose quarantine measures.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-moscow-deportation-idUSKCN20M252|title=Russia to deport 88 foreigners for violating coronavirus quarantine|date=28 February 2020|work=Reuters|access-date=29 February 2020|language=en}}</ref> Measures to prevent a crisis in Russia include banning the export of medical masks, random checks on the [[Moscow Metro]], and cancellation of large-scale events by schools. The Russian government has also taken measures to prevent foreign citizens from heavily affected countries from visiting Russia.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |title=Protect Putin from Covid-19: Kremlin's new mission as epidemic spreads worldwide |url=https://www.rt.com/russia/482289-protect-putin-from-covid/ |accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe Russian consumer health watchdog [[Rospotrebnadzor]] advised tourists to refrain from visiting Wuhan and stay away from Chinese zoos and markets selling animals and seafood. The agency also said that development of a vaccine against the virus was underway, relying on the WHO's recommendations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/01/22/russian-tourists-undeterred-from-china-despite-coronavirus-outbreak-a69007|title=Russian Tourists Undeterred From China Despite coronavirus pandemic|accessdate=25 January 2020|date=22 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/china-health-russia-vaccine/russia-is-developing-vaccine-against-coronavirus-ria-cites-regulator-idUSR4N29M01K|title=Russia is developing vaccine against coronavirus \u2013 RIA cites regulator|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123012316/https://www.reuters.com/article/china-health-russia-vaccine/russia-is-developing-vaccine-against-coronavirus-ria-cites-regulator-idUSR4N29M01K|archive-date=23 January 2020|accessdate=25 January 2020|agency=Reuters|date=22 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n144 Russians were evacuated from [[Wuhan]], the initial centre of the outbreak, and were quarantined in [[Tyumen Oblast]] for two weeks from 5 February.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russians Start 2-Week Coronavirus Quarantine After Return From Wuhan |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/02/05/russians-start-2-week-coronavirus-quarantine-after-return-from-wuhan-a69155 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=[[The Moscow Times]] |date=5 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 March, Russia temporarily banned the export of medical masks, gloves, bandages and protective suits.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 21 March, it was announced that Russia delivered over 100,000 test kits to 13 countries, including Armenia, Belarus, Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan, Serbia, Egypt, Venezuela, Iran, and North Korea.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia delivers over 100,000 Covid-19 test kits to 13 states, including Iran, North Korea |url=https://www.rt.com/russia/483701-russia-ships-coronavirus-testing/ |accessdate=21 March 2020 |work=[[RT (TV network)|RT]] |date=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, after a phone call with [[Italy|Italian]] Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]], Russian president [[Vladimir Putin]] arranged the Russian army to send medical help to Italy, which was the European country hardest hit by coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian army to send coronavirus help to Italy after Putin phone call |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia-italy/russian-army-to-send-coronavirus-help-to-italy-after-putin-phone-call-idUSKBN219081 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=22 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, [[Moscow Mayor]] [[Sergey Sobyanin]] told President Putin at a meeting that \"a serious situation is unfolding\" and that the relatively low number of confirmed cases could be due to a low level of testing, saying that \"there are far more people who are infected\" and that the number of people in Moscow suspected of having the coronavirus was about 500.<ref name=\"sobyanin-mar24\">{{cite website|url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/24/moscow-s-mayor-warns-putin-that-regional-officials-don-t-understand-coronavirus-risks-and-says-low-levels-of-testing-could-explain-russia-s-small-number-of-confirmed-cases|title=Moscow's mayor warns Putin that regional officials don't understand coronavirus risks and says low levels of testing could explain Russia's small number of confirmed cases|website=[[Meduza]]|date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://tass.com/society/1134701|title=No real picture of COVID-2019 situation in Russian regions \u2014 Moscow mayor|agency=[[TASS]]|date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://tass.com/society/1134671|title=About 500 people in Moscow suspected of having COVID|agency=[[TASS]]|date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Testing ===\n\nAs of 23 March, [[Russia]] has 4 testing systems and has carried out over 165 thousand tests for the coronavirus<ref name=\"test\">{{cite web |title=\u041e\u0431 \u0438\u0437\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0441\u0445\u0435\u043c\u044b \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0437\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u0443\u044e \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u044e \u0440\u0435\u0437\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0438\u0441\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0439 |url=https://rospotrebnadzor.ru/about/info/news/news_details.php?ELEMENT_ID=14090 |publisher=[[Rospotrebnadzor]] |accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Over 163,000 coronavirus tests carried out in Russia\">{{cite news |title=Over 163,000 coronavirus tests carried out in Russia |url=https://tass.com/society/1133655 |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=RUSSIAN NEWS AGENCY |language=en}}</ref> which is among the highest testing numbers in the world.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://ourworldindata.org/covid-testing |title = How many tests for COVID-19 are being performed around the world?}}</ref> Two private lab companies started testing on 26 March. According to Deputy Prime Minister [[Tatyana Golikova]], as of 25 March, 141 state laboratories were conducting tests in 79 federal subjects.<ref>{{cite news |title=Two Russian private labs launch coronavirus testing |url=https://tass.com/economy/1135125 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=25 March 2020}}</ref> There are plans to increase the number of reference centres across the country to 15.<ref name=\"mwt\"/><ref name=\"test\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u0434\u0438\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c COVID-19 \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0438\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0432 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0435 |url=https://www.interfax.ru/russia/700428 |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=[[Interfax]] |date=23 March 2020}}</ref> On 27 March, the [[Federal Service for Surveillance in Healthcare]] (Roszdravnadzor) registered two more test systems.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u044b \u0434\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |url=https://meduza.io/news/2020/03/30/v-rossii-zaregistrirovany-dva-novyh-testa-na-koronavirus |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nDr. Melita Vujnovic, the [[World Health Organization]]'s representative in Russia, stated that Russia, in accordance with WHO recommendations, \"started testing literally at the end of January.\u201d<ref name=\"Why does Russia, population 146 million, have fewer coronavirus cases than Luxembourg?, CNN\">{{cite news |title= Why does Russia, population 146 million, have fewer coronavirus cases than Luxembourg? |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/21/europe/putin-coronavirus-russia-intl/index.html |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=CNN |language=en}}</ref> Coronavirus testing in Russia was provided by the [[State Research Center of Virology and Biotechnology VECTOR]] in [[Novosibirsk]] and had to be verified there.<ref name=\"CNN Why\"/><ref name=\"NBC Russia's low infection\"/> There was concern that the tests may have insufficient sensitivity,<ref name=\"CNN Why\"/><ref name=\"NBC Russia's low infection\"/> despite the fact that the tests were verified in China since early February, showed the degree of sensitivity similar to or higher than other tests and the lab has been approved by the [[World Health Organization]].<ref name=\"CNN Why\"/> Since 23 March, [[European Russia]] doesn't send their batches to Novosibirsk for verification but verify them in a Moscow reference centre.\n\nThere was some skepticism about the accuracy of Russia's reported infection figures. Anastasia Vasilyeva, leader of the Doctors' Alliance organisation loosely aligned to the Russian opposition and doctor for opposition figure [[Alexei Navalny]], made a series of videos accusing the authorities of concealing the true number of coronavirus cases by using pneumonia and acute respiratory infection as a diagnosis instead. Health officials rejected the allegation, and President Putin addressed concerns about statistics, saying that the government is not covering up the number of cases, though might not have the full picture. The [[World Health Organization|WHO's]] representative to Russia, Dr. Vujnovic, also expressed skepticism at the allegation.<ref name=\"CNN Why\">{{cite news |last1=CNN |first1=Mary Ilyushina |title=Why does Russia, population 146 million, have fewer coronavirus cases than Luxembourg? |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/21/europe/putin-coronavirus-russia-intl/index.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=CNN}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC Russia's low infection\">{{cite news |title=Russia's low infection numbers viewed skeptically |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/coronavirus-russia-s-low-infection-numbers-viewed-skeptically-n1166101 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=NBC News |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"sobyanin-mar24\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/27/russias-coronavirus-cases-surpass-1000-in-biggest-one-day-jump-a69710|title=Russia's Coronavirus Cases Surpass 1,000 in Biggest One-Day Jump|website=[[The Moscow Times]]|date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Travel and entry restrictions ===\n[[File:COVID-19 pandemic in Moscow 24.03.20 005 (14).jpg|250px|thumb|[[Moscow Metro]] on 25 March]]\n[[File:COVID-19 pandemic in Moscow 24.03.20 005 (56).jpg|250px|thumb|[[Yaroslavsky suburban direction of Moscow Railway]] on 25 March]]\n\nOn 23 January, the Russian city of [[Blagoveshchensk]], near the [[China\u2013Russia border|Chinese border]], limited access to the country. [[Cultural diplomacy|Cultural exchange]] and official visits to China were cancelled. The Governors of the [[Amur Oblast|Amur Region]] [[Vasily Orlov]], and of the [[Penza Oblast]] [[Ivan Belozertsev]], called on residents to abandon trips to China altogether. Residents of large cities were told to avoid contact with tourists from China.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sputniknews.com/world/202001231078113159-you-shall-not-pass-russian-border-city-to-limit-access-to-china-due-to-coronavirus-outbreak/|title=You Shall Not Pass! Russian Border City to Limit Access to China Due to coronavirus pandemic|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123141329/https://sputniknews.com/world/202001231078113159-you-shall-not-pass-russian-border-city-to-limit-access-to-china-due-to-coronavirus-outbreak/|archive-date=23 January 2020|accessdate=25 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January, Deputy Prime Minister [[Tatiana Golikova]] said Russia will restrict the entry of foreigners arriving from [[China]], except for flights to [[Moscow Sheremetyevo Airport]].<ref name=\"mwt\">[https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/07/coronavirus-in-russia-the-latest-news-march-8-a69117 Coronavirus in Russia: The Latest News]</ref>\n\nOn 20 February, the entry of [[Chinese nationality law|Chinese citizens]] was banned. The temporary suspension is for Chinese citizens entering Russia for employment, private, educational and tourist purposes.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 28 February, Moscow announced that it would deport 88 foreigners for allegedly violating quarantine measures.<ref name=\":4\" /> Russia barred [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran|Iranian]] citizens from entering Russia and said it would also restrict the entry of [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Korea|South Korean]] citizens from 1 March. Flights between Russia and South Korea are suspended, except for those operated by [[Aeroflot]] and [[Aurora (airline)|Aurora]].<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 4 March, Russia suspended its train service from Moscow to [[Nice]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]].<ref name=\"mwt\" />\nAeroflot suspended flights to and from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Hong Kong|Hong Kong]] since 9 March.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nFlights to and from Italy, [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany|Germany]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain|Spain]] are limited since 13 March. Russia also stopped issuing tourist visas to Italian citizens and closed the border to Italian citizens and foreigners coming from Italy.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 15 March, the land borders with [[Norway\u2013Russia border|Norway]] and [[Poland\u2013Russia border|Poland]] were closed to all foreigners. [[Russian Railways]] announced it would stop passenger trains from [[Moscow]] to [[Berlin]] and [[Paris]]. Earlier it was announced that train connections to and from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Ukraine|Ukraine]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Moldova|Moldova]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Latvia|Latvia]] would be suspended because those countries had closed their borders.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nSince 16 March, flights to and from the [[European Union]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Norway|Norway]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Switzerland|Switzerland]] were limited to regular flights between capital cities ([[Geneva]] in the case of Switzerland) and [[Moscow Sheremetyevo Airport]], and charter flights.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia restricts air travel to the EU, allowing only charter flights and planes headed to capital cities |url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/13/russia-restricts-air-travel-to-the-eu-allowing-only-charter-flights-and-planes-headed-to-capital-cities |accessdate=13 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=13 March 2020}}</ref> [[Prime Minister of Russia|Prime Minister]] [[Mikhail Mishustin]] announced that [[Belarus\u2013Russia border|the border]] with [[Belarus]] has been closed for the movement of people and an entry ban for foreigners will be imposed from 18 March to 1 May.<ref>{{cite news|title=Russia closes border with Belarus over coronavirus|url=https://tass.com/politics/1130493|accessdate=15 March 2020|work=[[TASS]]|date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Russia to impose entry ban for foreigners from March 18 to May 1 |url=https://tass.com/society/1130915 |accessdate=16 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=16 March 2020}}</ref> On 17 March, [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Russia)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] said Russian embassies and consulates had stopped issuing all types of visas, including e-visas, with exceptions for diplomats, people attending funerals and transit passengers.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0417\u0430\u044f\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u041c\u0418\u0414 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u041c.\u0412.\u0417\u0430\u0445\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0432 \u0441\u0432\u044f\u0437\u0438 \u0441 \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435\u043c \u0432\u044a\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0443\u044e \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044e \u0438\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d \u0438 \u043b\u0438\u0446 \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 |url=https://www.mid.ru/ru/foreign_policy/news/-/asset_publisher/cKNonkJE02Bw/content/id/4089464 |publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Russia)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] |accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, Russia restricted [[air travel]] from all over the world, except for certain flights from Moscow to major capitals, and charter flights intended to move foreign citizens to their respective countries and [[Citizenship of Russia|Russian nationals]] back to Russia, until everyone is evacuated.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0430\u0432\u0438\u0430\u0441\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0441\u043e \u0432\u0441\u0435\u043c\u0438 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |url=https://ria.ru/20200323/1568989250.html |accessdate=23 March 2020 |agency=RIA Novosti |date=23 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, the Russian government loosened the travel ban to allow the entry for relatives of Russian citizens.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041a\u0430\u0431\u043c\u0438\u043d \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0440\u0435\u0448\u0438\u043b \u0432\u044a\u0435\u0437\u0434 \u0432 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0443 \u0438\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0430\u043c \u2014 \u0440\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430\u043c \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f\u043d \u041f\u043e\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043d\u0435\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0420\u0411\u041a |url=https://www.rbc.ru/society/26/03/2020/5e7cae179a794707bc5f7934 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[RBK Group|RBK]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAll regular and charter international flights were suspended on 27 March, except for those aimed at bringing Russians home.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian government rules to suspend all flights to foreign countries |url=https://tass.com/economy/1135639 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn the same day, [[Grozny Airport]] refused to receive passengers without permanent or temporary registration in Chechnya.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0410\u044d\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442 \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043d\u0435 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0430\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0430\u0436\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432 \u0438\u0437 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0432 \u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0435 - \u0430\u0434\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f |url=http://www.interfax-russia.ru/Moscow/special.asp?sec=1752&id=1117051 |accessdate=27 March 2020 |agency=Interfax |date=27 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nFollowing a request from the [[Government of Moscow]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0438 BlaBlaCar \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0432\u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0435\u0437\u0434\u043a\u0438 |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8079187 |accessdate=27 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=25 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> [[BlaBlaCar]] carpooling service decided to suspend its activities across Russia starting from 30 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Blablacar \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0443 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0430 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 |url=https://tass.ru/ekonomika/8100837 |accessdate=27 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=27 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, the Russian government decided to close all automobile, railway, pedestrian, river, or other [[border checkpoint]]s, including on the [[Belarus\u2013Russia border|Belarus border]], with exceptions similar to that of the air travel restrictions. The ban must be enforced on 30 March.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u044f\u0442\u043e \u0440\u0435\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u043c \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0434\u0432\u0438\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u0430\u0432\u0442\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0431\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0435, \u0436\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0437\u043d\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0436\u043d\u044b\u0435, \u043f\u0435\u0448\u0435\u0445\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0435, \u0440\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0438 \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0448\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442\u044b \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0443\u044e \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0443 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438, \u0430 \u0442\u0430\u043a\u0436\u0435 \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u0441\u0443\u0445\u043e\u043f\u0443\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0443\u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u043e\u043a \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e-\u0431\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044b |url=http://government.ru/docs/39307/ |website=Government of Russia |accessdate=28 March 2020 |language=ru |date=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Nationwide measures ===\n[[File:Vladimir Putin visited the Coronavirus Monitoring Center (2020-03-17) 06.jpg|thumb|250px|President Putin, Prime Minister [[Mikhail Mishustin]] and Moscow Mayor [[Sergey Sobyanin]] visited the Coronavirus Monitoring Center on 17 March]]\n[[File:\u041f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043b-\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430 \u0414\u0435\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u043e\u0445\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b (\u0421. \u0421\u043e\u0431\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d) 3.jpg|thumb|250px|Call centre for the coronavirus situation in Moscow at [[Khodynsky Boulevard]] located in the gym of school No. 1409.<ref>[https://www.kp.ru/daily/27103/4177306/ \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439 \u0421\u043e\u0431\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b call-\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440 \u043f\u043e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435: \u041c\u044b \u043f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043c \u044d\u0442\u0443 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043c\u0443]</ref>]]\n\nOn 14 and 15 March, [[Ministry of Education (Russia)|Ministry of Education]] and [[Ministry of Science and Higher Education (Russia)|Ministry of Science and Higher Education]] recommended regions to switch the educational process to [[distance learning]] if it is necessary.<ref name=\"mwt\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Moscow schools start rolling out 'flexible attendance' and remote learning policies to fight coronavirus spread |url=https://meduza.io/en/feature/2020/03/14/moscow-schools-start-rolling-out-flexible-attendance-and-remote-learning-policies-to-fight-coronavirus-spread |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, [[Ministry of Culture (Russia)|Ministry of Culture]] announced closing all cultural institutions under its jurisdiction, including museums, theaters, symphonies, and circuses.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia to close all federal theaters, museums, symphonies, and circuses |url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/17/russia-to-close-all-federal-theaters-museums-symphonies-and-circuses |accessdate=17 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=17 March 2020}}</ref> On the same day, President Vladimir Putin said that the situation was \"generally under control\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/63001|title=Meeting with Government members|date=17 March 2020|website=Kremlin.ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, [[Ministry of Education (Russia)|Minister of Education]] [[Sergey Kravtsov (politician)|Sergey Kravtsov]] announced that all Russian schools would be closed from 23 March to 12 April.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 19 March, Russia's [[Rospotrebnadzor|Chief Sanitary Doctor]] Anna Popova required all people arriving from abroad to undergo a two-week self-isolation.<ref>{{cite news |title=All people arriving in Russia must undergo 14-day self-isolation |url=https://tass.com/society/1132439 |accessdate=19 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=19 March 2020}}</ref> Russian courts stopped considering all but most urgent cases because of the pandemic until 10 April.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian Courts Put Most Work on Pause Over Coronavirus |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/19/russian-courts-put-most-work-on-pause-over-coronavirus-a69676 |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=[[The Moscow Times]] |date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, the Russian government adopted a number of decisions, including an instruction to regional authorities to suspend activities of any [[night club]]s, cinemas, children's entertainment centers, and to ban [[hookah]] smoking at any restaurants or cafes.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041e \u0440\u0435\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0445 \u043f\u043e \u0438\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0430\u043c \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043e\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0448\u0442\u0430\u0431\u0430 \u043f\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0443\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e \u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430 \u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0440\u0440\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0438 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=http://government.ru/orders/selection/401/39260/ |website=Government of Russia |accessdate=24 March 2020 |language=ru |date=24 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Central Bank of Russia|Central Bank]] recommended all the banks to keep the money for 3\u20134 days before giving it to clients or loading it into ATMs, and to restrict usage of cash recycling ATMs.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0420\u0435\u043a\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0431\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0430\u043c: \u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 |url=https://cbr.ru/press/event/?id=6561 |website=Central Bank of Russia |accessdate=24 March 2020 |language=ru |date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, President Putin, in a televised address to the nation, announced that the [[2020 Russian constitutional referendum]] would be postponed due to the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://tass.ru/politika/8075213|title=\u041f\u0443\u0442\u0438\u043d: \u0434\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\u043c \u043a \u041a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u043d\u0430 \u0431\u044b\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0435\u043d\u0430|agency=[[TASS]]|date=25 March 2020}}</ref> He added that the next week would be a nationwide paid holiday and urged Russians to stay at home.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://tass.com/society/1135339|title=Putin calls on Russians 'to stay home' due to coronavirus|agency=[[TASS]]|date=25 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"mt-mar25\">{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/25/coronavirus-in-russia-the-latest-news-march-25-a69117|title=Coronavirus in Russia: The Latest News - March 25|website=[[The Moscow Times]]|date=25 March 2020}}</ref> Putin also announced a list of measures of [[social protection]], support for [[small and medium-sized enterprises]], and changes in [[fiscal policy]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Address to the Nation |url=http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/63061 |website=President of Russia |accessdate=25 March 2020 |date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, [[Ministry of Science and Higher Education (Russia)|Minister of Science and Higher Education]] [[Valery Falkov]] ordered all universities to close from March 28 to April 5.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian students to go on recess on March 28 \u2014 April 5 |url=https://tass.com/society/1135613 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, as a follow-up to Putin's address to the nation, Prime Minister Mikhail Mishustin ordered all reservations at [[Pension (lodging)|pensions]] or [[Holiday cottage|holiday houses]] to be cancelled from 28 March to 1 June, recommended regional authorities to close all the [[piste]]s at resorts for the same period, instructed them to force all the public eating places (except for delivery services) to suspend activities from 28 March to 5 April, and recommend the citizens to refrain from travelling.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u041c\u0438\u0448\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0447\u0438\u043b \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043c\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0432 \u0441\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044f\u0445, \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0443 \u043a\u0443\u0440\u043e\u0440\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043e\u0431\u044a\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0442\u0434\u044b\u0445\u0430 \u0438 \u0434\u0435\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043e\u0440\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f |url=http://government.ru/orders/selection/401/39288/ |website=Government of Russia |accessdate=27 March 2020 |language=ru |date=27 March 2020}}</ref> On the same day, the Ministry of Education announced the postponement of the [[Unified State Exam]] from the end of May to the beginning of June.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041c\u0438\u043d\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0432\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0441\u043b\u043e \u0441\u0440\u043e\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0415\u0413\u042d |url=https://www.rbc.ru/society/27/03/2020/5e7dd7319a7947c713fa4a6a?utm_source=yxnews&utm_medium=desktop&utm_referrer=https%3A%2F%2Fyandex.ru%2Fnews |website=\u0420\u0411\u041a |accessdate=27 March 2020 |date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, as Moscow and Moscow Oblast declared a lockdown, Mishustin urged all regions to follow the example and take similar measures. He also announced a bill that would raise fines for breaching quarantine requirements.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041c\u0438\u0448\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u044b \u0431\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0435\u0440 \u0441 \u043c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 |url=https://www.interfax.ru/russia/701511 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=Interfax |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u041c\u0438\u0448\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b \u043e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0443\u044e \u0437\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0447\u0443 \u0432\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0439 \u0432\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u044f \u0440\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8111725 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March, the [[Federal Assembly (Russia)|Federal Assembly]] approved a law allowing the [[Mikhail Mishustin's Cabinet|executive cabinet]] to declare a state of emergency on its own. Previosly, only a commission led by the [[Minister of Emergency Situations (Russia)|Minister of Emergency Situations]] could do that.<ref>{{cite news |title=Legislation allowing prime minister's cabinet to declare state of emergency rockets through Russian legislative system |url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/31/legislation-allowing-prime-minister-s-cabinet-to-declare-state-of-emergency-rockets-through-russian-legislative-system |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza.io]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Lockdowns ===\n[[File:COVID-19 pandemic lockdowns in Russia.svg|350px|thumb|Map of federal subjects that have announced the \"self-isolation regime\".\n{{legend|#003557|Full lockdown}}\n{{legend|#278dbf|Partial lockdown}}]]\n\nOn 28 March, the Chechen authorities urged the population of the republic not to leave their places of permanent residence, and banned entry to [[Grozny]] for anyone except emergency services, food supplies, government officials, police, and journalists.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0427\u0420 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432\u044a\u0435\u0437\u0434 \u0432 \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043d\u044b\u0439 |url=https://chechnyatoday.com/news/334637 |accessdate=28 March 2020 |agency=\u0427\u0435\u0447\u043d\u044f \u0441\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044f |date=28 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> On the next day, [[Chechnya]] closed its borders, with a full lockdown coming into effect on 30 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia\u2019s Chechnya closes administratieve borders amid coronavirus outbreak |url=https://tass.com/russia/1137037 |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 March, Moscow issued a [[stay-at-home order]] for all residents starting on 30 March. Muscovites will not be allowed to leave their homes except in cases of emergency medical care and other threats to life and health, to travel to work for those who are obliged to, to make purchases in the nearest store or pharmacy, to walk pets at a distance not exceeding 100 metres from the place of residence, as well as to take out the garbage. People have to keep a distance of 1.5 metres. Recently unemployed will get 19,500 rubles a month.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441. \u041e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0432\u0438\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u043e \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0443 \u0438 \u0441\u043e\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u043a\u0430 |url=https://www.sobyanin.ru/koronavirus-ogranichenie-peredvizheniya-i-sospodderzhka-grazhdan |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=Sergey Sobyanin website |date=29 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0432\u0441\u0435\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0439 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://ria.ru/20200329/1569323145.html |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=\u0420\u0418\u0410 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438|date=29 March 2020}}</ref> After that, a similar regime was introduced in Moscow Oblast at 20:00 [[Moscow Time|MSK]] on 29 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0420\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0445 \u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 |url=https://mosreg.ru/sobytiya/novosti/news-submoscow/v-podmoskove-vvoditsya-rezhim-samoizolyatsii-dlya-vsekh-zhiteley |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=Governor of Moscow Oblast official website|date=29 March 2020}}</ref> Senator [[Andrey Klishas]], chair of the Federation Council Committee on constitutional legislation and state construction, criticized this decision, saying that such restrictions are the exclusive competence of the [[Federal Assembly (Russia)|Federal Assembly]] and the [[President of Russia|President]].<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041a\u043b\u0438\u0448\u0430\u0441 \u043e\u0431 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0445 \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435: \u0442\u0430\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u044b \u2014 \u0438\u0441\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0447\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u043d\u0446\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0430\u0440\u043b\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 |url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/4308072 |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=\u041a\u043e\u043c\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0442\u044a|date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, similar orders were announced in [[Adygea]], the [[Komi Republic]], [[Mari El]], [[Tatarstan]], [[Chuvashia]], some districts of [[Yakutia]], [[Arkhangelsk Oblast|Arkhangelsk]], [[Astrakhan Oblast|Astrakhan]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u0410\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0445\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |url=https://kaspyinfo.ru/srochnoe-zajavlenie-astrahanskaja-oblast-perehodit-na-rezhim-vseobshhej-samoizoljacii/ |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=KaspiyInfo |date=30 March 2020}}</ref> [[Belgorod Oblast|Belgorod]], [[Irkutsk Oblast|Irkutsk]], [[Kaliningrad Oblast|Kaliningrad]], [[Kursk Oblast|Kursk]], [[Lipetsk Oblast|Lipetsk]], [[Murmansk Oblast|Murmansk]], [[Nizhny Novgorod Oblast|Nizhny Novgorod]], [[Novgorod Oblast|Novgorod]], [[Ryazan Oblast|Ryazan]], [[Saratov Oblast|Saratov]], [[Sverdlovsk Oblast|Sverdlovsk]], [[Ulyanovsk Oblast|Ulyanovsk]] and [[Vologda Oblast|Vologda]] oblasts, the cities of [[Bryansk]] and Saint Petersburg.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0435 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438. \u0422\u0435\u043f\u0435\u0440\u044c \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 |url=https://fontanka.ru/2020/03/30/69060805/ |accessdate=30 March 2020 |publisher=Fontanka |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref><ref name=\"lockdown\">{{cite news |title=Which regions of Russia are sheltering in place? A running list |url=https://meduza.io/en/feature/2020/03/30/which-regions-of-russia-are-sheltering-in-place |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=30 March 2020}}</ref> [[Leningrad Oblast]] banned movement of people between districts and introduced a lockdown in the town of {{ill|Murino|ru|\u041c\u0443\u0440\u0438\u043d\u043e}}.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041b\u0435\u043d\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0441\u044f \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u0435\u0437\u0434 \u0437\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044b \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0436\u0438\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8115959 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March, the \"self-isolation regime\" was announced in republics of [[Altai Republic|Altai]], [[Bashkortostan]], [[Buryatia]], [[Dagestan]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u0414\u0430\u0433\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://ria.ru/20200331/1569421526.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> [[Ingushetia]], [[Kabardino-Balkaria]], [[Kalmykia]], [[Karachay-Cherkessia]], [[Republic of Karelia|Karelia]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://ria.ru/20200331/1569413191.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> [[Khakassia]], [[Mordovia]], [[Udmurtia]] and [[Tuva]], [[Altai Krai|Altai]], [[Khabarovsk Krai|Khabarovsk]] (for those over 65), [[Krasnodar Krai|Krasnodar]], [[Krasnoyarsk Krai|Krasnoyarsk]], [[Perm Krai|Perm]], [[Primorsky Krai|Primorsky]], [[Stavropol Krai|Stavropol]] and [[Zabaykalsky Krai|Zabaykalsky]] krais, [[Bryansk Oblast|Bryansk]], [[Chelyabinsk Oblast|Chelyabinsk]], [[Kaluga Oblast|Kaluga]], [[Kemerovo Oblast|Kemerovo]], [[Kirov Oblast|Kirov]], [[Kostroma Oblast|Kostroma]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://ria.ru/20200331/1569412562.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> [[Kurgan Oblast|Kurgan]], [[Magadan Oblast|Magadan]], [[Novosibirsk Oblast|Novosibirsk]], [[Omsk Oblast|Omsk]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412\u0441\u0435 \u0441\u0438\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u044b \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://ria.ru/20200331/1569414078.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> [[Penza Oblast|Penza]], [[Pskov Oblast|Pskov]] (for those over 65), [[Rostov Oblast|Rostov]], [[Sakhalin Oblast|Sakhalin]], [[Samara Oblast|Samara]], [[Smolensk Oblast|Smolensk]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u0421\u043c\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0432\u0441\u0435\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0439 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://ria.ru/20200331/1569419173.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> [[Tambov Oblast|Tambov]], [[Tomsk Oblast|Tomsk]], [[Vladimir Oblast|Vladimir]], [[Volgograd Oblast|Volgograd]] and [[Voronezh Oblast|Voronezh]] oblasts, [[Khanty-Mansi Autonomous Okrug|Khanty-Mansi]]<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u042e\u0433\u0440\u044b \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430 |url=https://ria.ru/20200331/1569419723.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> and [[Yamalo-Nenets Autonomous Okrug|Yamalo-Nenets]] autonomous okrugs, the [[Jewish Autonomous Oblast]],<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u0415\u0432\u0440\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0430\u0432\u0442\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u043e\u0434\u044f\u0442 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8125851 |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref> the city of [[Sevastopol]].<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u0421\u0435\u0432\u0430\u0441\u0442\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0435 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |url=https://ria.ru/20200331/1569417054.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u0420\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u044b \u0432\u0432\u043e\u0434\u044f\u0442 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0443 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b |url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/4309220 |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[Kommersant]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u0420\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d \u0432 51 \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0435 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 |url=https://riafan.ru/1263791-rezhim-samoizolyacii-vveden-v-51-regione-rossii |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RIA FAN]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"lockdown\" /> Republics of Yakutia and Karelia limited the sale of alcohol.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0438\u043b \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0436\u0443 \u0430\u043b\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e\u043b\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u044f \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 |url=https://www.rbc.ru/society/31/03/2020/5e836ed79a7947715cc2f33c |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[RBK Group|RBK]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Local measures ===\n\nOn 24 March, [[Chechnya]] became the first region to close restaurants and cafes.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\n==== Moscow and Moscow Oblast ====\n[[File:Vladimir Putin in Kommunarka hospital1.jpg|250px|thumb|President Putin visits coronavirus patients at Moscow hospital on 24 March]]\n[[File:Vladimir Putin in Kommunarka (2020-03-24) 10.jpg|250px|thumb|Denis Protsenko (middle), the medical director of the Kommunarka hospital visited by President Putin (left) and Moscow Mayor Sobyanin (right), was tested positive for the coronavirus]]\n{{multiple image\n | width = 250\n | direction = vertical\n | image1 = \u0421\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430 \u0432 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 (1).jpg\n | caption1 = Construction of an infection centre in [[Moscow]] in connection with the spread of coronavirus started on March 12.<ref>[https://meduza.io/news/2020/03/12/v-novoy-moskve-nachali-stroit-bolnitsu-dlya-gospitalizirovannyh-iz-za-koronavirusa \u0412 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u043d\u0430\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0443 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0433\u043e\u0441\u043f\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430]</ref> The photo shows progress as of March 16, 2020.\n | image2 = \u0421\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430 \u0432 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 (21 \u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430; \u0410. \u0411\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0451\u0432) 1.jpg\n | caption2 = March 21, 2020.\n | footer = \n}}\nMoscow started the construction of a special hospital for the coronavirus patients near the villages of {{ill|Babenki (Moscow)|lt=Babenki|ru|\u0411\u0430\u0431\u0435\u043d\u043a\u0438 (\u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0430)}} and {{ill|Golokhvastovo (Voronovskoye Settlement)|lt=Golokhvastovo|ru|\u0413\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0445\u0432\u0430\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043e (\u043f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0412\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435)}} in [[Troitsky Administrative Okrug]].<ref>[https://www.sobyanin.ru/koronavirus-stroitelstvo-novoi-infektsionnoi-bolnitsy \u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441. \u041e\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u043e\u0449\u0430\u0434\u043a\u0430 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044b]</ref><ref>[https://tass.ru/moskva/7969335 \u041f\u043b\u043e\u0449\u0430\u0434\u044c \u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u044f\u0449\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0441\u044f \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430 \u0432 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442 43 \u0433\u0430]</ref>\n\nFrom the beginning of the outbreak, Moscow patients have been brought to newly-constructed buildings of the City Hospital No. 40 in the district of [[Kommunarka]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Moscow hospital set aside for coronavirus patients |url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/03/moscow-hospital-set-aside-for-coronavirus-patients |accessdate=16 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=16 March 2020}}</ref> The Mukhin and Yudin City Hospitals, City Hospital No. 52,<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u044b \u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0433\u043b\u0438 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044e \u043e \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446 |url=https://ria.ru/20200310/1568400914.html |accessdate=25 March 2020 |agency=RIA Novosti |date=25 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> Maxillofacial Hospital for War Veterans, Infectious Hospitals No. 1 and 2, Bashlyaeva Children's Hospital, City Hospital No. 67, and the [[Sklifosovsky Institute]]<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041e\u0442\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0435\u0439 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u044b\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u043c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0435 \u2116 67 |url=https://tass.ru/moskva/8055337 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=23 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> are also receiving patients suspected to have COVID-19. On 27 March, the [[Nil Filatov|Filatov]] Hospital No. 15 has been fully transformed to receive them as well.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439 \u0421\u043e\u0431\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u044b\u043b \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0440 \u0432 \u0413\u041a\u0411 \u211615 \u0438\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430 |url=https://www.mskagency.ru/materials/2987627 |accessdate=27 March 2020 |agency=AGN Moscow |date=27 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> On 30 March, four institutions of the [[Federal Biomedical Agency]] started to receive coronavirus patients only \u2014 the Burnazyan Medical Biophysical Center, Otolaryngology Center, and Hospital No. 85 in Moscow, as well as the Scientific Hi-tech Centre in Moscow Oblast.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u044b\u043b\u0438 \u0442\u0440\u0438 \u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430 \u0442\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043a\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u043c \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |url=https://ria.ru/20200330/1569343619.html |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=RIA Novosti |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March, [[Mayor of Moscow]] [[Sergei Sobyanin]] announced a \u201chigh alert regime\u201d, ordering self-isolation for two weeks for [[Russians]] returning from China, South Korea, Iran, France, Germany, Italy and Spain.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 10 March, Mayor Sobyanin signed a decree for banning mass events in [[Moscow]] with more than 5,000 participants from 10 March to 10 April.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0430\u0442 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0435 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0440\u0438\u044f\u0442\u0438\u044f \u0441 \u0447\u0438\u0441\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c\u044e \u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0435 \u043f\u044f\u0442\u0438 \u0442\u044b\u0441\u044f\u0447 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a|url=https://www.mos.ru/news/item/70786073/|trans-title=Mass events in Moscow with more than 5000 participants will be limited.|accessdate=12 March 2020 |work=mos.ru|date=5 February 2020|language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, the Governor of Moscow Oblast [[Andrey Yuryevich Vorobyov|Andrey Vorobyov]] has announced a high alert status, banning large events with over 5,000 people.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nSince 16 March, school attendance was optional in Moscow and Moscow Oblast. According to [[RBK Group|RBK]], Moscow recommended that private schools go on a two-week holiday or switch to distance learning. On 21 March, schools were closed for three weeks.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 16 March, Moscow extended measures to closing [[State school#Russia|public schools]], athletic schools and supplemental education institutions from 21 March to 12 April; banning indoor events with more than 50 attendees and all outdoor mass events. The compulsory 14-day self-isolation which had been previously enforced to people coming [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in China|China]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Korea|South Korea]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran|Iran]], was extended to those coming from the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|United States]] and all European countries.<ref>{{cite news |title=Moscow extends coronavirus measures to ban outdoor events, close schools, and isolate all U.S. and European arrivals |url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/16/moscow-extends-coronavirus-measures-to-ban-outdoor-events-close-schools-and-isolate-all-u-s-and-european-arrivals |accessdate=16 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, Mayor Sobyanin ordered all people over 65 to self-isolate at home starting Thursday, saying each would receive 4,000 [[Russian ruble|rubles]] (around $50) for following the order.<ref name=\"mwt\" /> He also suggested that older residents leave Moscow and stay in their [[dacha]]s. School students' public transportation cards were temporarily suspended, starting from the 5th grade.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia to use mobile phones to track people at risk of coronavirus |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia/russia-to-use-mobile-phones-to-track-people-at-risk-of-coronavirus-idUSKBN21A1MT |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=23 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441. \u041e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043a \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0448\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u043f\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e. \u041c\u0435\u0440\u044b \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u043a\u0438 \u0441\u0435\u043c\u0435\u0439 \u0441 \u0434\u0435\u0442\u044c\u043c\u0438 |url=https://www.sobyanin.ru/koronavirus-obraschenie-k-starshemu-pokoleniyu-i-semyam-s-detmi |website=\u0421\u0430\u0439\u0442 \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u044f \u0421\u043e\u0431\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |language=ru |date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, it was announced that Moscow hospitals would receive up to 200,000 rubles (around $2,500) for each coronavirus patient from the city's health insurance fund.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.interfax.ru/moscow/700670|title=\u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044b \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0442 \u0434\u043e 200 \u0442\u044b\u0441. \u0440\u0443\u0431. \u043d\u0430 \u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043a\u0430\u0436\u0434\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c|agency=[[Interfax]]|date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, following the respective decision of the federal government, Mayor Sobyanin ordered the closure of all municipal libraries and clubs, as well as cinemas and night clubs, banned hookah smoking in cafes, and suspended any organized leisure social activities, including [[amusement park]]s. He also instructed [[dental clinic]]s to see patients with acute pain or other emergencies only. Municipal multiservice centers suspended services, except for those unavailable online. Free or concessionary use of public transport was suspended for people aged over 65, with chronic diseases, students of [[vocational school]]s or [[high school]]s.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441. \u0417\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u0438\u0435 \u0431\u0438\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043e\u0442\u0435\u043a, \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0438 \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u0438\u0435 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f 25.03.2020 |url=https://www.sobyanin.ru/koronavirus-ogranicheniya-250320 |website=\u0421\u0430\u0439\u0442 \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u044f \u0421\u043e\u0431\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |language=ru |date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, Mayor Sobyanin ordered restaurants, cafes, bars, canteens, parks, commercial and retail businesses requiring personal attendance, except those providing essential services, like grocery shops and pharmacies, to close during the week from 28 March to 5 April, the holiday week announced by President Putin.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441. \u0417\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u0438\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0438 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432 |url=https://www.sobyanin.ru/koronavirus-zakrytie-restoranov-i-parkov |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=Sergey Sobyanin website |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===== Accusations of ethnic profiling at the earlier stages =====\nIn February, it was reported that drivers of [[Mosgortrans]] were required to inform their dispatchers if they see Chinese nationals in their vehicles, for police to be called.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u0432\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0430\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0431\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0432 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043e \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0435 \u043c\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0430\u0436\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432-\u043a\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0439\u0446\u0435\u0432. \u0412 \"\u041c\u043e\u0441\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0441\u0435\" \u043e\u0431\u044a\u044f\u0441\u043d\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u044d\u0442\u043e \"\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435\u043c \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0444\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\" |url=https://novayagazeta.ru/news/2020/02/19/159209-v-moskve-voditeli-avtobusov-rasskazali-o-prikaze-monitorit-passazhirov-kitaytsev-v-mosgortranse-eto-otritsayut |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=Novaya Gazeta |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref><ref name=\"Meduza_Chinese\" /> [[Moscow Metro]] employees were required to ask Chinese nationals to fill in questionnaires.<ref name=\"Meduza_Chinese\">{{cite web |last1=\u041a\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0446\u043e\u0432\u0430 |first1=\u0418\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0430 |last2=\u041b\u043e\u0445\u043e\u0432 |first2=\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0440 |title=\"\u041d\u0430 \u043c\u0435\u043d\u044f \u043e\u0437\u0438\u0440\u0430\u044e\u0442\u0441\u044f, \u043a\u0430\u043a \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043a\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\". \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0432\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0439\u0446\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0432\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0435, \u043d\u043e \u0442\u0435 \u044d\u0442\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0442\u0438 \u043d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438. \u0417\u0430\u0442\u043e \u0437\u0430\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438, \u043a\u0430\u043a \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u044f\u043b\u043e\u0441\u044c \u043e\u0442\u043d\u043e\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043a \u043d\u0438\u043c |url=https://meduza.io/feature/2020/02/21/na-menya-ozirayutsya-kak-na-prokazhennogo |publisher=Meduza |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=ru |date=21 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 February, Mayor Sobyanin confirmed that Mosgortrans and Moscow Metro were asked to work together with police forces to \"monitor those who arrived from China\". Facial recognition was also used to track these people.<ref name=\"Meduza_Chinese\" />\n\nOn 24 February, [[Embassy of China, Moscow|the Chinese Embassy in Russia]] asked Moscow authorities to put an end to these \"excessive measures\" in transport.<ref name=\"mwt\" /> Sobyanin insisted that the measures were not discriminatory but helped control those who were required to stay self-isolated upon arrival from China.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0421\u043e\u0431\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d \u043e\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u044c\u0431\u0443 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u043a\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0439\u0446\u0435\u0432 |url=https://www.rbc.ru/society/26/02/2020/5e56c8ba9a794750c67274b8 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=RBC |date=26 February 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nIn early March, numerous cases of deportation of Chinese students who allegedly broke the quarantine rules were reported.<ref>{{cite web |last1=\u0411\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0445\u0438\u043d |first1=\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440 |title=\u0422\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0446 \u0441 \u0434\u0435\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u0439. \u041a\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0443\u044e \u0441\u0442\u0443\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0443 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0438\u0437 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0436\u0438\u0442\u0438\u044f, \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0448\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0435\u0439 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d \u0438 \u0432\u044b\u0434\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0438\u0437 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u044b |url=https://zona.media/article/2020/03/11/deportations |publisher=Mediazona |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=ru |date=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0435\u0432 |first1=\u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0439 |last2=\u041c\u0438\u0448\u0438\u043d\u0430 |first2=\u0412\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0440\u0438\u044f |title=\u041d\u0435 \u041a\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0439 \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434 |url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/4284597 |publisher=Kommersant |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=ru |date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nHowever at the later stages many of these Russian measures were applied to all foreign arrivals, including for Russian citizens coming back from abroad, with them being forced into self quarantine and facecam profiling. 200 cases of quarantine-breakers by Russian citizens were reported to be recognized with facecam profiling, tracked by Public surveillance cameras in Moscow.<ref>{{cite web |title=Russia to quarantine all arrivals from abroad for two weeks |url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-03/19/c_138895937.htm |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus Outbreak Is Major Test for Russia\u2019s Facial Recognition Network |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/25/coronavirus-outbreak-is-major-test-for-russias-facial-recognition-network-a69736 |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==== Saint Petersburg and Leningrad Oblast ====\n\nOn 13 March, the governors of Saint Petersburg and Leningrad Oblast [[Alexander Beglov]] and [[Aleksandr Drozdenko]] announced a high alert status and banned events with more than 1,000 and 300 people respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0435 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u043f\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430. \u041c\u0435\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0440\u0438\u044f\u0442\u0438\u044f \u0441 \u0443\u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0435\u043c \u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0435 \u0442\u044b\u0441\u044f\u0447\u0438 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a \u0437\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u044b |url=https://meduza.io/news/2020/03/13/v-peterburge-vvedut-rezhim-povyshennoy-gotovnosti-iz-za-koronavirusa |accessdate=13 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, Governor of Saint Petersburg Alexander Beglov banned events and gatherings with more than 50 people.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 26 March, he ordered restaurants, cafes, bars, canteens, parks, [[Place of worship|places of worship]], commercial and retail businesses requiring personal attendance, except those providing essential services, like grocery stores and pharmacies, to close during the holiday week from 28 March to 5 April. Free and concessionary tickets for public transport will be suspended during the week. Leisure facilities including night clubs, children's playrooms, and recreation centres will be closed until 30 April. In Leningrad Oblast only pharmacies, grocery stores, building material and household stores will remain open during the holiday week.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u043e\u044e\u0442 \u0432\u0441\u0435, \u043a\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0443\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u043c\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0437\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0438 \u0430\u043f\u0442\u0435\u043a |url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/4302162 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[Kommersant]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 April, the [[Saint Petersburg Metro]] will start closing on 22:00 [[Moscow Time|MSK]] instead of 0:00\u20130:45 MSK. The ground transportation will end on 23:00 MSK and its intervals will be increased.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0421\u043c\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0443\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043b \u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u044b \u0434\u043b\u044f \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430. \u041c\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435\u0442 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u0432 22:00 |url=https://www.fontanka.ru/2020/03/31/69062962/ |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[Fontanka]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Economic impact ==\n\nOn 20 February, [[Ministry of Finance (Russia)|Minister of Finance]] [[Anton Siluanov]] said Russia is losing around 1 billion [[Russian ruble|rubles]] each day because of decreased trade with China.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia losing 1 bln roubles a day in trade with China over coronavirus - minister |url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/health-pmn/russia-losing-1-bln-roubles-a-day-in-trade-with-china-over-coronavirus-minister |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[National Post]] |date=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 March, the head of the Russian Association of Tour Operators said [[Tourism in Russia|Russia's tourism sector]] had already taken a 27 billion ruble hit from the impact of the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus Hits Russian Tourism for $400M Loss |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/05/coronavirus-hits-russian-tourism-for-400m-loss-a69537 |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[The Moscow Times]] |date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs a result of the pandemic, factory output and transportation demand fell, bringing overall demand for oil down as well, and causing oil prices to fall. This triggered an [[OPEC]] summit in [[Vienna]] on 5 March. At the summit, OPEC agreed to cut oil production by an additional 1.5 million barrels per day through the second quarter of the year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/05/opec-meets-to-decide-whether-to-cut-output-as-coronavirus-hits-demand.html|title=Oil drops as OPEC agrees on massive oil supply cut to offset virus impact; awaits Russia's approval|last=Ellyatt|first=Sam Meredith,Holly|date=2020-03-05|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=2020-03-10}}</ref> OPEC called on Russia and other non-OPEC members of OPEC+ to abide by the OPEC decision.<ref name=Reuters_120320>{{cite web |title=OPEC and how it has dealt with oil price crashes |url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/finance/other/opec-and-how-it-has-dealt-with-oil-price-crashes/ar-BB1162HQ |website=Reuters |accessdate=12 March 2020 |date=12 March 2020}}</ref> On 6 March, Russia rejected the demand, marking the end of the partnership, with oil prices falling 10% after the announcement.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-51774622|title=Oil plunges 10% after Opec deal collapses|date=2020-03-06|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-10|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Reed|first=Stanley|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/06/business/opec-oil-prices-russia.html|title=Oil Prices Nose-Dive as OPEC and Russia Fail to Reach a Deal|date=2020-03-06|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-03-11|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> On 8 March, [[Saudi Arabia]] initiated an [[2020 Russia\u2013Saudi Arabia oil price war|oil price war]] with Russia, triggering a major fall in the [[price of oil]] around 30%.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/08/investing/oil-prices-crash-opec-russia-saudi-arabia/index.html|title=Oil crashes by most since 1991 as Saudi Arabia launches price war|last=Business|first=Matt Egan, CNN|website=CNN|access-date=2020-03-10}}</ref> The price war is one of the major causes of the currently ongoing [[2020 stock market crash|global stock market crash]]. As the result of the oil price falling, the Russian ruble suffered a fall hitting a four-year low against the [[U.S. dollar]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian Ruble Plummets Amid Oil Market Chaos |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/09/russian-ruble-plummets-amid-oil-market-chaos-a69562 |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[The Moscow Times]] |date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, First Deputy [[Ministry of Transport (Russia)|Minister of Transport]] and [[Federal Air Transport Agency]] head Alexander Neradko said cancellation of international flights during the pandemic threatens to bankrupt multiple Russian airlines. Russian airlines lost an estimated 1.7 billion rubles due to the cancelation of flights to China in February. According to Neradko, airlines could lose another 100 billion rubles in revenues by the end of the year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Air travel cancellations could bankrupt multiple Russian airlines |url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/17/air-travel-cancellations-could-bankrupt-multiple-russian-airlines |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, Russia's federal list of \u201csystemically important\u201d companies was expanded to three times, featuring about 600 businesses. According to [[Vedomosti]], the updated list includes new airlines ([[Rossiya Airlines|Rossiya]], [[S7 Airlines|S7]], [[Utair]]), airports ([[Moscow Domodedovo Airport|Moscow Domodedovo]], [[Pulkovo Airport|Saint Petersburg Pulkovo]]), grocery store chains ({{ill|Vkusvill|ru|\u0412\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0432\u0438\u043b\u043b}}, [[Auchan]]), fast food chains ([[McDonald's]], [[Burger King]]), and retail stores ({{ill|Sportmaster|ru|\u0421\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u043c\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0440}}, [[IKEA]]).<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia expands its list of 'systemically important' companies, adding McDonald's, IKEA, and more |url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/23/russia-expands-its-list-of-systemically-important-companies-adding-mcdonald-s-ikea-and-more |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, [[Mayor of Moscow]] [[Sergei Sobyanin]] issued orders to support businesses which include postponing payments on organizations\u2019 property and land taxes, deferring rental payments, reducing payments fixed in trading contracts and extending the deadlines for paying trade fees. On 25 March, [[President of Russia]] [[Vladimir Putin]] announced following measures for microenterprises, small- and medium-sized businesses: deferring tax payments (except Russia's [[value-added tax]]) for the next six months, cutting the size of social security contributions in half, deferring social security contributions, deferring loan repayments for the next six months, a six-month moratorium on fines, debt collection, and creditors\u2019 applications for bankruptcy of debtor enterprises. Additionally, a new tax on income from large deposits will be introduced in 2021, and the tax on offshores will be increased.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0420\u0430\u0437\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0431\u044f\u0442 \u0438 \u0443\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0443\u0442: \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0432\u043a\u043b\u0430\u0434\u043e\u0432 \u0432\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433 |url=https://www.gazeta.ru/business/2020/03/26/13023967.shtml?utm_source=yxnews&utm_medium=desktop&utm_referrer=https%3A%2F%2Fyandex.ru%2Fnews |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[Gazeta.ru]] |date=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title='They need to quarantine Moscow' How small businesses in Russia's capital are scrambling to stay afloat as coronavirus clobbers the economy |url=https://meduza.io/en/feature/2020/03/27/they-need-to-quarantine-moscow |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Bankrolling Russia's relief program Putin has proposed sweeping tax cuts to shore up vulnerable businesses as coronavirus cripples the economy, but a lot more might be needed and it's unclear who would foot the bill |url=https://meduza.io/en/feature/2020/03/26/bankrolling-russia-s-relief-program |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[Meduza]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=How Putin's Higher Tax on Offshore Gains May Help Russia Weather the Economic Storm Amid COVID-19 |url=https://sputniknews.com/analysis/202003251078708415-how-putins-higher-tax-on-offshore-gains-may-help-russia-weather-the-economic-storm-amid-covid-19/ |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[Sputnik News]] |date=25 March 2020}}</ref> On 27 March, the Association of Banks of Russia reported an increase of deposits closure.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0411\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0436\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u044c \u0432 \u0426\u0411 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u044f\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043a\u043b\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u043e \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u0438\u0438 \u0432\u043a\u043b\u0430\u0434\u043e\u0432 |url=https://www.rbc.ru/finances/27/03/2020/5e7ce4369a794723cb66f2db |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[RBK Group|RBK]] |date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, associations of companies of [[online shopping]], [[retail]], [[Hospitality industry|culinary]] and nine other industries sent a letter to Prime Minister Mishustin, in which they warned of a possible collapse of their businesses and asked for numerous additional measures of support.<ref>{{cite web |last1=\u0412\u0438\u0440\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e |first1=\u041a\u0441\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f |title=\u0420\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0439\u043b \u0438 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0443\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043e \u0440\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043b\u043b\u0430\u043f\u0441\u0430 \u0432 \u043e\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043b\u0438 |url=https://www.vedomosti.ru/business/articles/2020/03/25/826222-riteil-i-obschepit |website=Vedomosti |accessdate=27 March 2020 |language=ru |date=25 March 2020}}</ref> On 26 March, a petition signed by publishing houses and book stores pleading for support was published.<ref>{{cite web |title=\"\u041a\u043d\u0438\u0436\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u044b\". \u0411\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0435 \u0441\u043e\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043a\u043d\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0438\u0437\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0446\u043e\u0432 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0441\u044c \u043a \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0443 \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430: \u043f\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0446\u0438\u044f |url=https://novayagazeta.ru/articles/2020/03/26/84529-petitsiya-predstaviteley-knizhnogo-biznesa-rossii |website=Novaya Gazeta |accessdate=27 March 2020 |language=ru |date=26 March 2020}}</ref> On 30 March, owners of hotels and restaurants asked the government for 1-year [[tax deferral]] and other fiscal measures.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0446 \u0438 \u043e\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0441\u044c \u0432 \u043a\u0430\u0431\u043c\u0438\u043d \u0441 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u044c\u0431\u043e\u0439 \u043e \u043d\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u043b\u044c\u0433\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0445 |url=https://tass.ru/ekonomika/8119231 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=30 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\n[[Aeroflot]]\u2032s [[low-cost carrier]] [[Pobeda Airlines]] announced it would stop flights on 1 April until 31 May.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0410\u0432\u0438\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \"\u041f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u0430\" \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0442 \u0432\u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0442\u044b \u0441 1 \u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u043b\u044f |url=https://www.vedomosti.ru/business/articles/2020/03/27/826449-loukoster-pobeda-priostanovil-poleti |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=[[Vedomosti]] |date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Sberbank]] and [[VTB Bank]] with backing from the [[Central Bank of Russia|Central Bank]] will start offering six-month, interest-free loans to businesses to help them pay employee salaries.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russia's State Banks to Offer Interest-Free Salary Loans |url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/26/russias-state-banks-to-offer-interest-free-salary-loans-a69764 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[The Moscow Times]] |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Social impacts ==\n\n=== Event cancellations ===\nOn 5 March, First Deputy Prime Minister [[Andrey Belousov]] announced cancelling [[St. Petersburg International Economic Forum]] which was due to be held from 3 to 6 June 2020.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nOn 11 March, Russian Defence Minister [[Sergey Shoygu]] cancelled the [[Moscow International Security Conference]] which had been scheduled for 22 to 23 April.<ref name=\"mwt\" />\n\nAs [[TASS]] reported on 17 March, all football, hockey and basketball games were suspended until 10 April.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0420\u041f\u041b, \u041a\u0425\u041b \u0438 \u0415\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043b\u0438\u0433\u0430 \u0412\u0422\u0411 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0442\u0447\u0438 \u0434\u043e 10 \u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u043b\u044f |url=https://tass.ru/sport/8001241 |accessdate=17 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=17 March 2020}}</ref> On the same day, [[UEFA]] confirmed postponing [[Euro 2020]] until summer 2021, one of the venues of which is [[Krestovsky Stadium]] in Saint Petersburg.<ref>{{cite news |title=Euro 2020 postponed until next summer, Uefa confirms |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51909518 |accessdate=17 March 2020 |work=[[BBC]] |date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nDespite the fact that a [[conscription]] started on 1 April, conscipts won't be sent to duty stations until 20 May.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0428\u043e\u0439\u0433\u0443 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b \u043e\u0442\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u044f\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u044b\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0432 \u0432\u043e\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u0440\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0435 20 \u043c\u0430\u044f |url=https://tass.ru/armiya-i-opk/8126011 |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=[[TASS]] |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Religious services ===\nOn 17 March, the [[Holy Synod of the Russian Orthodox Church]] instructed the clergy to use disposable [[Plastic cup|cups]], [[Medical glove|gloves]], and [[facial tissue]] during sacraments and celebrations, disinfect church plates and premises regularly, and refrain from offering the [[Hand-kissing|hand for kissing]]. The partakers were encouraged to refrain from kissing the [[Cup#Religious use|cup]] and the [[Christian cross|cross]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Instructions to rectors of parishes and monasteries' town churches, abbots and abbesses of the monasteries of the Russian Orthodox Church over the threat of spreading coronavirus infection |url=http://www.patriarchia.ru/en/db/text/5608615.html |publisher=Russian Orthodox Church |accessdate=24 March 2020 |date=17 March 2020}}</ref> On 30 March, [[Patriarch Kirill]] urged people not to visit churches.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0430\u0440\u0445 \u041a\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043b\u043b \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b \u0432\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u043e\u0442 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0445\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0432 |url=https://ria.ru/20200329/1569309684.html |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=[[RIA Novosti]] |date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nWhen in St. Petersburg attendance of places of worship was restricted on 26 March, the Church deemed it unlawful.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0435 \u0443\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043c\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0421\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0442-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0430, \u0441\u043e\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0430\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0445\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0432 |url=http://www.patriarchia.ru/db/text/5613196.html |publisher=Russian Orthodox Church |accessdate=29 March 2020 |language=ru |date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nHowever, on 29 March, [[Patriarch Kirill of Moscow|Patriarch Kirill]] told the faithful to refrain from going to church.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0430\u0440\u0445 \u041a\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043b\u043b \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b \u0432\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u043e\u0442 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0445\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0432 |url=https://ria.ru/20200329/1569309684.html |accessdate=29 March 2020 |agency=RIA Novosti |date=29 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nVarious Muslim communities closed their mosques. In Moscow, the [[Moscow Cathedral Mosque|Cathedral Mosque]], the [[Old Mosque, Moscow|Old Mosque]], and the Memorial Mosque on [[Poklonnaya Hill]] closed on 18 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u043b\u0438\u0441\u044c \u043c\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438 \u041f\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u0430\u0439\u0442\u0435 \u0418\u0410 IslamNews:https://islamnews.ru/news-v-moskve-zakrylis-mecheti |url=https://islamnews.ru/news-v-moskve-zakrylis-mecheti |accessdate=24 March 2020 |agency=Islam News |date=18 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> On 23 March, mosques in [[Republic of Crimea|Crimea]] and [[Sevastopol]] were shut down.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041c\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438 \u041a\u0440\u044b\u043c\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u043e\u044e\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0440\u0438 \u043d\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |url=https://ria.ru/20200323/1569017296.html |accessdate=24 March 2020 |agency=RIA Novosti |date=23 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> On the next day, all the mosques in [[Krasnodar Krai]] and [[Adygea]] were closed as well.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041c\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438 \u0432 \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u0435 \u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u041a\u0443\u0431\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u044b \u0432 \u0441\u0432\u044f\u0437\u0438 \u0441 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/8067163 |accessdate=24 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=24 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> Same measures are planned in Dagestan.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432 \u0414\u0430\u0433\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0435: \u0432 \u0440\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0435 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0440\u0443\u044e\u0442 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u044c \u043c\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438 |url=https://news-r.ru/news/dagestan/464469/ |accessdate=24 March 2020 |agency=\u0420\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d Online |date=24 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, Rabbi [[Berel Lazar]] closed the [[Bolshaya Bronnaya Synagogue]], [[Marina Rosha Synagogue (Moscow)|Maryina Rosha Synagogue]], and Zhukovka Jewish Center.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0421\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0430 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0435\u0432\u0440\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0438\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0442\u0430 \u0432 \u0446\u0435\u043b\u044f\u0445 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |url=https://tass.ru/moskva/8013291 |accessdate=24 March 2020 |agency=TASS |date=18 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref> It was reported that 11 members of the community were hospitalized, with four COVID-19 cases confirmed, with the first one being a rabbi who felt sick after Purim celebration on 9 March.<ref>{{cite web |last1=\u0420\u0435\u043f\u0438\u043d\u0430 |first1=\u0421\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0430 |title=\u0416\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0432\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u043e \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0435 \u043c\u0443\u0436\u0430: \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0440\u0443\u0448\u0438\u043b \u043b\u0435\u0433\u043a\u0438\u0435 |url=https://www.mk.ru/social/2020/03/24/zhena-ravvina-moskovskoy-sinagogi-rasskazala-o-koronaviruse-muzha-razrushil-legkie.html |website=Moskovsky Komsomolets |accessdate=24 March 2020 |language=ru |date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0412 \u043c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0435 \u043b\u0438\u043a\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0438\u0440\u0443\u044e\u0442 \u043e\u0447\u0430\u0433 COVID-19 |url=http://www.ng.ru/faith/2020-03-22/1_7823_synagogue.html |website=Nezavisimaya Gazeta |accessdate=24 March 2020 |language=ru |date=22 March 2020}}</ref> On 24 March, Rabbi [[Berel Lazar]] and the [[Federation of Jewish Communities of Russia|Federation of Jewish Communities]] recommended all the synagogues to close down and the community centers and Jewish schools to switch to [[distance education]].<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u0435\u0432\u0440\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0438\u043d \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u043b\u0430 \u0432\u0441\u0435 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0438 \u0441\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0438 \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 |url=https://www.interfax.ru/russia/700732 |accessdate=24 March 2020 |agency=Interfax |date=24 March 2020 |language=ru}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Russia]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Russia]]\n[[Category:2020 in Russia]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Russia]]\n", "name_user": "213.87.158.94", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Russia"}
